{
  "texts": [
    "Pooled estimations did not show a higher incidence of NICU hospitalizations and even showed a lower incidence among vaccinated pregnant persons at 3T and 2,3T (RR 0.92; 95% CI 0.87-0.97 and RR 0.92; 95% CI 0.87-0.97, respectively) [Fig.",
    "S16 of the ESM].",
    "A subgroup analysis by vaccine platform and vaccine status did not show any relevant difference between groups.Only one study reported adjusted effect measures for respiratory distress in the newborn (not due to COVID-19) [43] and one reported for infant death [51] among pregnant persons receiving mRNA vaccination at any trimester.",
    "There was no increased risk (RR 0.84; 95% CI 0.42-1.68).The background rates of infant safety outcomes were within the CIs of the proportional meta-analysis performed (see Table S9 of the ESM).",
    "Data were analyzed by trimester of exposure and vaccine type."
  ]
}